    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-05T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-05T09:00:00-05:00" n="802"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114A/219</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-05T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 5, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 7, 4.41 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5057. For War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="#p_DEL1"
                    >Dresel</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 205. Inter-Ally Commission of Berne has refused all applications, principally
                    originating with Y.M.C.A. here, to send to Russian prisoners in Germany articles
                    of any nature, including such as are used for religious services. I concur fully
                    but at instance of Doctor <persName corresp="#p_HAC1">Harte</persName> I request
                    definite ruling from you on subject. <persName corresp="#p_DEL1"
                        >Dresel</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SPA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stovall</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
